comment.en: the current air pollution represented as European Air Quality Index value. The index value is based on 3 pollutants of major concern in Europe: PM10, NO2, O3 and will be able to take into account to 3 additional pollutants (CO, PM2.5 and SO2) where data are also available.

comment.undefined: An event happening at a certain time and location, such as a concert, lecture, or festival. Ticketing information may be added via the [[offers]] property. Repeated events may be structured as separate Event objects.
A person.
Represents concepts which directly represent pollution. For example the concentration of pollutants at a particular spatio-temporal point.

Represents concepts which indirectly contribute to pollution of a place. These do not directly represent pollution but have properties which can affect the pollution, for example by changing the concentration of pollutants at a spatio-temporal point.
Will capture things like education level, majority types of jobs
A subset of spatio-temporal trajectory points represent a TrajectorySegment
Observation represents a spatio-temporal observation of pollutants under time and place parameters.
Represents a trajectory of points. Examples include drainage/sewage trajectory or air stream trajectory.
A collection of spatio-temporal points represents a trajectory

Represents various pollutants which contaminate the environment and directly represnt/contribute to pollution. Additionally a carrier's trajecectory point may pick up pollutants from a spatio-temporal point, in which case, it is represented by the sub-property carriesPollutant.
